page.title: 01Addlethorpe, Lincs
page.content: This area is mainly rural with scattered farms and is criss crossed by dykes and minor roads. The land is flat and used mainly for cereal farming and cattle grazing. On the Eastern side is a sewage farm which serves the local area. Traffic in the area increases during the summer period and is often delayed by farm vehicles, eg., tractors and combine harvesters serving the farms. R A F aircraft are frequently flying over the area to practice firing and bombing at Wainfleet Bombing Range a little further down the coast, disturbing the area's peace and tranquility.
